        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         You can do it at full spawn, it just takes leet skills, or something.  Also, it requires level 60 and your epic and CoS at the least, and a good bit of HP and preferably a full spell book (Funeral Pyre is the shit.)</P><P>I recommend lots of EEs the first time you try.  Also, don't do a west wall break, make it up north and FD /q out and clear from there.</P><P>Its also significantly easier when you don't have the golems and CT up.  Agro is strange here so if you FD without /q'ing out chances are you are getting agroed by every farkin mob in the zone and if a golem is up DTed.</P><P>Take advantage of the fact that mobs take full damage from dots while moving now too, if they resist root a lot just snare em and forget about root, run around (presuming you are in a clear area.)</P><P>Read up about all the mobs first too.  For example, don't turn your back to the little red drakes. ;)</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
