        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This is how I solo break it.  Ive done it numerous times.</P><P>I have Epic, FP, CoS, Run 3, Elder beads.   (Ive done without FP and run 3 but they sure do help)</P><P>Now, bind at the bind rock in Ferrott.</P><P>Zone in and run to the west wall camp, Imediatly FD and /q weather you think you got agro or not.</P><P>When you get back look around at what you have.  There should be an assling somewhere off to your left.  This is the first thing you want dead.</P><P>Look around for an undead, If none are available, Pull the assling with FP and root.  Then Snare, and stack every dot in your arsonal on it.  If you get adds, Root park them and mez them but get the assling dead no matter what.</P><P>When you kill it, FD /q or Gate and zone back in and run to camp.</P><P>With him dead your pretty much able to pull anything wandering from your right or left without agroing half the zone.</P><P>Try to pull to the left first, Its easier, much less asslings to worry about.</P><P>If you get lucky enough to get an undead on a pull of two, Charm it with thrall.  If too high, use Endslave.  Charm is your friend in Fear.</P><P>By the way, Dont even think about trying to solo Fear with CT or Draco up, Its just not worth the headache.  The golems might DT you now and then so carry some EEs. (One of the reasons I have a pet that procs ageo and comlete heal)</P><P>Anyway, it takes a lot of practuice.  Dont be afraid to gate and try again, Die'ing is no fun.  Naked CRs are dangerous as hell.</P><P>-Tekai, Warlock of Vice $$   Drinal Server</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=253063" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.kurious-krimes.net/images/tekai.jpg" alt="Tekai`s Magelo Profile."></a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
