        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Everytime I've zoned into PoF and cast harmshield, no matter where I was, I would get DTed. It's weird. However in the event you do not get DTed, upon zoning in and casting HS, you will not make it to the north wall before it wears off and you will have a truckload of mobs on your tail. You should not be aggroing the undead on the initial break, however shiverbacks, scarelings and spiders will probably chase you. </P><P>I'm actually in PoF right now solo, just got to north wall and /q-ed and it kicked me to desktop so I'm visiting here. 56 with epic. It's hard but certainly doable.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
